cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks in image recognition and the vulnerability of these networks to adversarial examples. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the potential for adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a technique for improving the robustness of deep neural networks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
